.venv 
venv
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Python
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# Distribution / packaging
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment & secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
*.env.local

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor / IDE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS-specific
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Package manager lock/cache (uv, since you're using uv.lock)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: uv.lock is usually fine to COMMIT (it pins reproducible
# dependency versions, like package-lock.json). Listed here only
# as a comment so you know it's a deliberate choice, not an oversight.
# uv.lock

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project-specific: don't commit large/sensitive personal data
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment if your data/ folder ever contains real company
# documents you don't want public on GitHub:
# data/